(1, 'OBJ', 'BECE', 'YrK13', 'ENG', 3, '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px\">PART A - COMPREHENSION</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><em>Read the following passage and answer the questions on it.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Perseverance is a quality which anybody who intends to succeed in any venture must possess. Indeed, lack of this great asset has been repoinsible for the failure of many people. A lot of things can be achieved through perseverance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It is the determination to endure all types of situations so as to achieve the desired goal. When in spite of obstacles in one&#39;s way, one determines to succeed, the person then perseveres. The consequence of such determination is success.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A farmer who cannot persevere cannot reap a bountiful harvest. Apart from preparing the land, he has to plant the crops, weed the farm, prune the plants if need be, toil day and night to take care of the plant, ultimately he gets a good harvest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Similarly, a student who wants to excel must possess the quality of perseverance. he has to obey instructions of his teachers, do all assignments, be all ears in the classroom. he has to burn the midnight oil, overcome all obstacles on his way, as a result of his relentless efforts, he performs brilliantly in his examination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A lazy student is not willing to persevere. he comes to school irregularly, and doesn&#39;t pay attention to his teacher&#39;s instructions. While his mates are reading in the night, he is snoring. When examination comes, he will want to cheat or use the &quot;giraffe&quot; method to pass, he will eventually be caught and will be full of sorrow and regrets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Any businessman who gives up after some setbacks cannot make it. There are bound to be obstacles in any venture and when they are overcome, a person becomes wealthy. So an individual must make up his mind to persevere. many people who are poor have not learnt to persevere. They try to venture and when there are initial failures or setbacks, they give up. So they contract disease called poverty. Don&#39;t give up, persevere.</p>'),
(1, 'OBJ', 'BECE', 'YrK14', 'ENG', 3, '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px\">PART A</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px\">SECTION 1 - COMPREHENSION</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><em>Read this passage carefully and answer the questions on it.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Teaching today is a very interesting and&nbsp;<u>challenging</u>&nbsp;job, because the students of today are the leaders of tomorrow. People used to thing that&nbsp;<u>students were like empty buckets;</u>&nbsp;all the teacher had to do was to fill the buckets with the waters of knowledge or information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">These days, teaching and the learning process is very different, it is true that the teachers have to provide information, but students have to process that information, if it is to be remembered and used.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The students process the information by first understanding it, then they have to think about it, and see how they can remember it, and use it. So, providing information, or knowledge, is not enough. Teachers have also to teach skills and attitudes to their to their students.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Teachers have to teach skills such as social skills to avoid and to resolve conflicts in the society and attitudes to themselves, their friends and relations, community, country and even the world. Remember, no one else can make us better people except ourselves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><em>(Adapted from &quot;Junior English Project for Junior Secondary School Bk 1)</em>&nbsp;</p>'),
