(1, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK07', 'VBA', 2, '<p><strong><em>Read this passage carefully and answer the questions that follow.</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are so used to seeing fire everywhere that we may think that there was never a time when men did not use fire. Yet there was such a time. In the beginning, men did not know about fire. Food was eaten raw. In the cold months, too, there was no fire to keep them warm. They kept warm by wrapping themselves in animal skin and furs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At last men found out how yo make fire. This may have come by accident. It is likely that someone threw a hard stone against another and saw sparks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Man is a thinking being and may have thought out that the new thing which he had invented could be used in many ways.</p>'),
