(1, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK08', 'VBA', 2, '<p><strong>SECTION A</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>In each of the following questions, words are paired. Choose from the words given the one which is most suitably fits as pair.</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Example:&nbsp;</em></strong>He and man, she and&nbsp;<u>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</u></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">A.aunt</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">B.girl</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">C.mother</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">D woman</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">E queen</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The suitable word is woman.</p>'),
(1, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK09', 'ENG', 2, '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><strong>SECTION 1</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><u><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px\">PASSAGE A</span></strong></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Read the following passages carefully and answer the questions that follow by choosing the most appropriate of the options lettered A-E (Nos. 1-10)</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr. and Mrs. Akinwale had been married for seven years. They lived in a village called Erele. They had only one child. His name was Segun. He was two and a half years old, the villagers called them &#39;Baba segun&#39;and &#39;Mama Segun&#39;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Baba Segun, who was a farmer, was the only male child of his father. Baba Segun was only sixteen years old when his father died. Though he was young, he was strong and hardworking. he had also learnt a lot from his late father. Therefore, it was not difficult for him to support his widowed mother and his sister.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He took over his father&#39;s farms. These included a palm tree plantation, a cocoa plantation and another farm for food crops.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cocoa trees were yound and tender; his father just planted them a year before he died. However, they were protected by&nbsp;banana trees which had been planted earlier to provide shade for the young seddlings. Akinwale took good care of the plantations.</p>'),
(1, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK09', 'VBA', 2, '<p><strong>SECTION A</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>In each of the following questions, two incomplete words are given. Choose from the options lettered A-E, the one that will correctly complete the first word and begins the second.</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>An example is given below:</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rai(&nbsp; &nbsp; )</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; a</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;m</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; e</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;A.c</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;B.f</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;C.n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;D.s</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;E.t</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The only letter that best complete the first word and begins the second is &quot; n&quot; which is lettered &quot; C&quot; . We would therefore shade answer space on the answer sheet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now answer question numbers 1-10.</p>'),
(1, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK10', 'ENG', 2, '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:24px\"><strong>SECTION 1</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Read the following passage carefully and answer the questions that follow:</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>One day, the hare approached the tortoise and said, &quot;come, let us have a race.&quot; The tortoise agreed and asked, &quot;Where shall we begin?&quot; The hare replied, &quot;We shall begin under that orange tree and race to the mango tree in the chief&#39;s compound.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Therefore, the race began. Of course, the hare soon left the tortoise far behind. But as he ran, he said to himself &quot;I am going too fast, I will lie down and have a little rest.&quot; He lay down and soon fell asleep. All this while, the tortoise had been coming along very, very slowly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eventually, he arrived at the place where the hare was fast asleep and he passed through and, finally at the mango tree in the chief&#39;s compound, he confidently sat down to await the arrival of the hare. When, at last, the hare did arrive and found the tortoise had won after all, he was very angry with himself for being so careless as to let a mere tortoise beat him.</p>'),
(1, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK10', 'VBA', 2, '<p><strong>SECTION A</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>In each of the following items of five words lettered A-E, one of the word is a general term which describes what the other words are, pick the correct one that describes the other words.</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Example:&nbsp;</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(a) Mars ( b) Planet ( c) Sun ( d) Venus (e) Saturn</p>\r\n\r\n<p>B is the correct option for &quot;Planet&quot; describes the other words.</p>'),
(1, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK11', 'ENG', 2, '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:24px\"><strong>SECTION 1</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><u>PASSAGE A</u></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Read these passages and answer the questions that follow:</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Taking an examination is one of the ways a student can be promoted to the next class. It is used to give a final certificate to a student who has completed studies in a school. There are different ways pupils can prepare for their examinations. They should read their books and listen to their teachers. Doing their homework and asking questions in class will also help them. They should write their notes correctly and neatly. Neat and clear writing will make the pupils enjoy reading. Only lazy pupils will waste their time and start getting ready when they have less than two weeks to their examination.</p>'),
