(1, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK12', 'ENG', 2, '<p><u><strong>SECTION 1</strong></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>PASSAGE A</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Read the following passages below carefully and answer the questions that follow by choosing from letters A - E (Nos. 1-10)</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><u>AKIN AND THE STOLEN MEAT</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once upon a time, there was a boy called Akin. Akin had a bad habit that of dipping his fingers into soup pots; whether it was his mother&#39;s or any other one. Soup would go sour and their owners would be wondering what went wrong.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Akin continued with this habit ntil he was caught red-handed one sunny afternoon, with meat stuck in his throat in a neighbour&#39;s kitchen. When the owner of the kitchen came in and saw Akin trying hard to spit out the meat, she started shouting, thief! thief!! thief!!! People gathered and some tried to get the meat out but could not. Surprisingly, when the woman tried, out came the meat!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Akin was beaten and made to dance around the village square with empty milk cans and leaves hung around his neck. By evening that day, he was on his knees crying and begging for forgiveness. He was forgiven and he promised to stop stealing. Not long after, Akin began to preach against all forms of bad habits to his friends.</p>'),
