(11, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK09', 'VBA', 2, '<p><strong>SECTION B</strong><strong><em>??</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>In each of the following questions, there is a pair of words followed by another pair which is not complete. Study the first pair carefully and choose from the options lettered A-E, the one that best completes the second pair.</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>An example is given below.</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mummy and daddy, daughter and&nbsp;<u>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</u></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A. Brother</p>\r\n\r\n<p>B. Cousin</p>\r\n\r\n<p>C. Nephew</p>\r\n\r\n<p>D. Son</p>\r\n\r\n<p>E. Uncle</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The word that best completes the second pair is &quot; son&quot;. Answer space D would therefore be shaded on the answer sheet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now answer the question numbers 11-15</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),
