(11, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK10', 'VBA', 2, '<p><strong>SECTION C</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>In each of the following questions, two incomplete words are given. Choose from the options lettered A-E the one that will correctly complete first word and begins the second.</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Example:&nbsp;</em></strong>Be(&nbsp; )I&#39;ve</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;i</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;f</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; e</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;( a)&nbsp; a</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;( b)&nbsp; e</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;( c) l</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;( d) m</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;( e) n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The only letter that best completes the first word and begins the second is &quot; l&quot; which is letter &quot; C&quot;.</p>'),
