(11, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK14', 'VBA', 2, '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>SECTION C</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><strong>In each of the following questions, choose the word that cannot be formed by an arrangement of some or all of the letters of the word printed in CAPITAL letters. Do not use any letter more often than it appears in the given word</strong></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><strong>An Example is given below:</strong></em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;\">EDUCATION</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;\">A. action</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;\">B. auction</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;\">C. caution</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;\">D. date</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;\">E. lotion</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>The word that cannot be formed by an arrangement of some or all of the letters of the word EDUCATION is \'lotion\'. We would, therefore, shade the answer space E on the answer sheet.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Now answer questions 11-15</p>'),
