(21, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK09', 'VBA', 2, '<p><strong>SECTION D</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>In each of the following questions, choose the word that CANNOT be formed by an arrangement of some or all of the letters of the word written in capital letters. DO NOT use any letter more often than it appears in the given word.</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>An example is given below:</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>DESCRIBE</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A.Beer</p>\r\n\r\n<p>B.Bees</p>\r\n\r\n<p>C. Drive</p>\r\n\r\n<p>D. Rice</p>\r\n\r\n<p>E. Side</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The word that cannot be formed by an arrangement of some or all of the letters of the word DESCRIBE is &quot; drive &quot; . We would therefore shade answer space C on the answer sheet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now answer question numbers 21-25.</p>'),
(21, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK10', 'VBA', 2, '<p><strong>SECTION E</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>In each of the following questions there is a pair of words followed by another pair which is not complete. Study the first carefully and chose from the options lettered A-E the one that best completes the second pair.&nbsp;</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Example:&nbsp;</em></strong>Book and Library, Animal and&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A. Cage</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;B. Forest</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; .&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; C. Garden</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;D. Hole</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;E. Zoo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>The word that best completes the second pair is &quot; Zoo &quot; which is lettered &quot; E&quot;. Now answer questions 21-25.</em></p>'),
(21, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK11', 'QTR', 2, '<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:22px\">SECTION E</span></strong></p>'),
