(21, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK12', 'VBA', 2, '<p><strong>SECTION E</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>There are three sentences in each of the following questions. Read them carefully and choose which one should come first, second and then third.</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>An example is given below:</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1.I went to the market to buy some oil.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2.There was no oil in the market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">3.I wanted to cook soup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">(a) 1,2,3</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">(b) 1,3,2</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">(c)2,3,1</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">(d) 3,1,1</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">(e) 3,2,1</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The correct answer is E that is&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. I wanted to cook soup</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. There was no oil in the market</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. I went to the market to buy some oil.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We would therefore shade answer space E on the answer sheet. Now answer questions 21-25.</p>'),
