(31, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK08', 'VBA', 2, '<p><strong>SECTION F</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Choose the word that cannot be formed by an arrangement of some or all of the letters of the word printed in capital letters. Do not use any letter more often than it appears in the word printed in capital letters.</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Example:&nbsp;</em></strong>Teacher</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A. each</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; B. cheer</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; C. chair</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; D. reach</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; E. heat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The answer is &#39; C&#39; there is no &#39; i&#39; in teacher.</p>'),
(31, 'OBJ', 'NCEE', 'YrK09', 'VBA', 2, '<p><strong>SECTION F</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Each of the following questions consists of five words lettered A-E. four of them have at least some thing in common while the fifth one is odd. Pick out the one that does NOT belong to the group.</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>An example is given below:&nbsp;</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A. Cow</p>\r\n\r\n<p>B. Dog</p>\r\n\r\n<p>C. Goat</p>\r\n\r\n<p>D. Sheep</p>\r\n\r\n<p>E. Snake</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The word that does NOT belong to the group is &quot; snake&quot; which is lettered E. We would therefore shade answer space E on the answer sheet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now answer question numbers 31-35.</p>'),
