(6, 'OBJ', 'GBK', 'Yr1', 'BLS', 5, '<p>Matthew 26:69-74</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text Matt-26-69\"><sup class=\"versenum\">69&nbsp;</sup>Now <strong>Peter</strong> was sitting out in the courtyard, and a servant girl came to him. &ldquo;You also were with Jesus of Galilee,&rdquo; she said.</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"en-NIV-24125\" class=\"text Matt-26-70\"><sup class=\"versenum\">70&nbsp;</sup>But he denied it before them all. &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t know what you&rsquo;re talking about,&rdquo; he said.</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"en-NIV-24126\" class=\"text Matt-26-71\"><sup class=\"versenum\">71&nbsp;</sup>Then he went out to the gateway, where another servant girl saw him and said to the people there, &ldquo;This fellow was with Jesus of Nazareth.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"en-NIV-24127\" class=\"text Matt-26-72\"><sup class=\"versenum\">72&nbsp;</sup>He denied it again, with an oath: &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t know the man!&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"en-NIV-24128\" class=\"text Matt-26-73\"><sup class=\"versenum\">73&nbsp;</sup>After a little while, those standing there went up to Peter and said, &ldquo;Surely you are one of them; your accent gives you away.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"en-NIV-24129\" class=\"text Matt-26-74\"><sup class=\"versenum\">74&nbsp;</sup>Then he began to call down curses, and he swore to them, &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t know the man!&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text Matt-26-74\">Immediately a rooster crowed</span></p>'),
