(6, 'OBJ', 'WASSCE', 'YrK18', 'ENG', 1, '<p>The word trivial means;&nbsp; of little value or importance,&nbsp;of&nbsp;very&nbsp;little&nbsp;importance&nbsp;or&nbsp;value;&nbsp;insignificant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>synonyms:unimportant,&nbsp;insignificant,&nbsp;inconsequential,&nbsp;minor,&nbsp;of no/little account,&nbsp;of no/little consequence,&nbsp;of no/little importance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>while&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Heavy means;&nbsp;of&nbsp;major&nbsp;import;&nbsp;grave;&nbsp;serious</p>'),
(7, 'OBJ', 'GBK', 'Yr1', 'BLS', 5, '<p>Genesis 3:1-6</p>\r\n<p class=\"chapter-1\"><span class=\"text Gen-3-1\">Now the <strong>serpent&nbsp;</strong>was more crafty than any of the wild animals the&nbsp;<span class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>&nbsp;God had made. He said to the woman, &ldquo;Did God really say, &lsquo;You must not eat from any tree in the garden&rsquo;?&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"en-NIV-58\" class=\"text Gen-3-2\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2&nbsp;</sup>The woman said to the <strong>serpent</strong>, &ldquo;We may eat fruit from the trees in the garden,</span><span id=\"en-NIV-59\" class=\"text Gen-3-3\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3&nbsp;</sup>but God did say, &lsquo;You must not eat fruit from the tree that is in the middle of the garden, and you must not touch it, or you will die.&rsquo;&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"en-NIV-60\" class=\"text Gen-3-4\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4&nbsp;</sup>&ldquo;You will not certainly die,&rdquo; the <strong>serpent</strong> said to the woman.</span>&nbsp;<span id=\"en-NIV-61\" class=\"text Gen-3-5\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5&nbsp;</sup>&ldquo;For God knows that when you eat from it your eyes will be opened, and you will be like God,&nbsp;knowing good and evil.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span id=\"en-NIV-62\" class=\"text Gen-3-6\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6&nbsp;</sup>When the woman saw that the fruit of the tree was good for food and pleasing to the eye, and also desirable&nbsp;for gaining wisdom, she took some and ate it. She also gave some to her husband,&nbsp;who was with her, and he ate it.</span></p>'),
